05/10/2004
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Naser Oric, the former commander of the Muslim forces in Srebrenica, is to appear before the UN tribunal on Wednesday (6 October) to answer war crimes charges.
He is charged with destroying 50 Serb villages and driving their population out of the area.
He is also accused of failing to prevent cruel treatment and killings of Serb prisoners by troops under his command.
Oric was arrested and transferred to The Hague in April 2003.
(AFP - 04/10/04)
